yoshioka.js is javascript MVC framework for client-side webapp based on YUI 3.
some text

Quick documentation to use with Git :

For development environnement, you need a web server with rewriting, php and node.js.
For building, you need java.
For production, you need only a static web server.

Development environnement :
- create a new folder for your project, then init a git repository :

$ mkdir mywebapp
$ cd mywebapp
$ git init

- add git submodule into your app

$ git submodule add git://github.com/hadrienl/yoshioka.js.git

- create your app

$ cp yoshioka.js/dist/* .

- if you use Apache, you can copy .htaccess file too

$ cp yoshioka.js/dist/.htaccess

- If you use another webserver, like Cherokee, read the htaccess and try to get the same thing ;)

Your app is ready to use. Configure it now !
Edit the config/app_config.js file

$ vi config/app_config.js

- replace 'yourapp' by the namespace of your app. Choose a short name, it's a namespace for all your classes.
- You can make the config file and load your app :

$ node yoshioka.js/tools/make/init.js

Load your browser !


